description.narrative: The Gambia currently does not report on child poverty since the country is yet to conduct or adopt either child friendly monetary poverty analysis or a Multidimensional Overlapping Depreciation analysis (MODA). Poverty figures are often derived from existing national statics such as the IHS and MICS and child poverty is not disaggregated but rather children are included in overall household poverty data. As poverty affects children differently to adults and the rest of the population it is important to put in place measures to bring out issues affecting children and support government agencies leverage more funding for children. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:20/01/2020
